<h2>Motivation</h2><p>
Voter turnout is low in the US. Midterm elections typically draw about 40 percent of the eligible public and in 2014 turnout was only 36.4 percent. Social pressure has been shown to successfully and dramatically <a href="http://isps.yale.edu/research/publications/isps08-001#.VGGBB1PF-bQ"><it>motivate potential voters</a>. So share this app and help me leverage social pressure to improve civic engagement in our democracy.
<p>
